en_802086_0	Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, Commander of the Army on Monday (12) afternoon paid a courtesy call on the newly-appointed Secretary Defence, Mr Hemasiri Fernando at his office in the Ministry of Defence.
en_802086_1	During the formal meeting, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake briefly enlightened Mr Fernando on the present day roles and tasks of the Army as well as its dedicated commitment towards reconciliation gestures in the North and East.
en_802086_2	Mr Fernando expressed his appreciation towards the services, being rendered by the Army and assured his continued cooperation for smooth conduct of affairs in the organization in future too.
en_802086_3	Towards the end of the interaction, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake extending his greetings on his appointment presented a memento to Mr Fernando as a gesture of goodwill.
